   \end{tabular}
    \caption{Ages of Urban Campus students}
   \label{tab:t3_4}
\end{table}

\item $median = \frac{23 + 24}{2} = 23.5 $

\end{itemize}

The {\bf{median}} is the center score of the distribution.  Half of the values are below the median and half are above the median in the distribution. 

\begin{itemize}
\item Strength:  It is RESISTANT to extreme value (\emph{outliers}).

